President Obama has announced his intent to nominate Elisabeth Hagen for the position of Under Secretary of Agriculture for Food Safety at the Department of Agriculture. Hagen is currently the USDA's Chief Medical Officer and has experience in developing and executing food safety agendas. She has also worked in the private and academic sectors as a physician. Hagen holds an M.D. from Harvard Medical School.

The President also intends to nominate Michele M. Leonhart for the position of Administrator of Drug Enforcement at the Drug Enforcement Administration (DEA), Department of Justice. Leonhart has almost 30 years of experience as a Special Agent with the DEA and has served in various management roles. She was the first female Special Agent in Charge and has received several awards for her work in federal law enforcement. Leonhart holds a B.S. in Criminal Justice from Bemidji State University.